  "body": "# Problem\r\nDuring the process of swapping over form ganache-core to buidler, we have noticed two things:\r\n1. Some of our test suite that should be passing (tested against ganache, geth, parity) is now failing.\r\n2. Tests now take 2-3 times slower to run\r\nA draft pull request has been opened [here](https://github.com/smartcontractkit/chainlink/pull/2427) for easy diffing.\r\n\r\n# Steps to reproduce\r\n1. Clone the chainlink repository:\r\n```sh\r\ngit clone git@github.com:smartcontractkit/chainlink.git\r\n```\r\n2. Checkout buidler branch\r\n```sh\r\ngit checkout feature/buidler\r\n```\r\n3. Install dependencies\r\n```sh\r\nyarn\r\nyarn setup:contracts\r\n```\r\n4. Run tests\r\n```sh\r\nyarn workspace @chainlink/contracts test\r\n```\r\n5. Observe failing tests, and the test time.\r\n6. Checkout the commit before the buidler conversion\r\n```sh\r\ngit checkout HEAD^\r\n```\r\n7. Repeat steps 3-4\r\n8. Observe passing tests and faster test time.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
